flowRoot.flowPara: Cockpit is the modern Linux admin interface. We release regularly. Here are the release notes from version 173.
The Storage page now shows an “Install VDO support” link if the VDO package is not installed. This is similar to the on-demand installation of the NFS client packages in Cockpit 169.

text.tspan: Machines: Add disks to a virtual machine

flowRoot.flowPara: The “Disks” tab of a virtual machine now has an “Add Disk” button. Using this new feature, it’s possible to create a virtual disk in a libvirt storage pool or attach an existing disk.
